<item>
            <title>[PIG-3136] Introduce a syntax making declared aliases optional</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PIG-3136</link>
                <project id="12310730" key="PIG">Pig</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;This is something Daniel and I have talked about before, and now that we have the @ syntax, this is easy to implement. The idea is that relation names are no longer required, and you can instead use a fat arrow (obviously that can be changed) to signify this. The benefit is not having to engage in the mental load of having to name everything.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;One other possibility is just making &quot;alias =&quot; optional. I fear that that could be a little TOO magical, but I welcome opinions.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
